248
00:14:00,914 --> 00:14:04,001
This job goes south,
there well may not be another.

249
00:14:04,668 --> 00:14:07,462
So here is us,
on the raggedy edge.

250
00:14:08,922 --> 00:14:12,050
Don't push me,
and I won't push you.

251
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:14,261
[Speaking Chinese]

252
00:14:26,815 --> 00:14:30,277
Zoe, Wash gonna straighten
this boat out before
we get flattened?

253
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:33,906
(Zoe)
Like a downy feather, sir.
No one flies like my mister.

254
00:14:34,072 --> 00:14:35,949
[Engine grinding]

255
00:14:36,491 --> 00:14:39,077
[Mal and Zoe chattering]

256
00:14:43,081 --> 00:14:44,082
(Simon)
River.

257
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:48,337
I know.
We're going for a ride.

258
00:14:50,505 --> 00:14:52,382
[Engine revving]

259
00:15:01,225 --> 00:15:03,352
[People chattering]

260
00:15:07,731 --> 00:15:09,775
Hey, little one.

261
00:15:11,151 --> 00:15:13,320
Understand your part
in all this?

262
00:15:15,697 --> 00:15:16,740
Do you?

263
00:15:18,492 --> 00:15:20,285
This is what I do, darling.

264
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:25,332
This is what I do.

265
00:15:27,918 --> 00:15:29,336
(Mal)
Let's move, people.

266
00:15:30,629 --> 00:15:33,090
Quit fiddling.
Want the boat running
smooth when we get back.

267
00:15:33,173 --> 00:15:35,801
Have faith, Captain.
Not today.

268
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,679
Pair of clips
in the rear hatch.

269
00:15:39,930 --> 00:15:42,516
We should hit town
right during Sunday worship.

270
00:15:42,599 --> 00:15:43,934
Won't be any crowds.

271
00:15:44,017 --> 00:15:46,311
If Fanty and Mingo
are right about the payroll...

272
00:15:46,395 --> 00:15:48,438
this could look to be
a sunny day for us.

273
00:15:48,522 --> 00:15:50,399
(Simon)
River, stay behind the others.

274
00:15:50,482 --> 00:15:53,485
If there's fighting,
drop to the floor or run away.

275
00:15:54,528 --> 00:15:56,530
It's okay
to leave them to die.

276
00:15:56,864 --> 00:16:00,325
Doctor, I'm taking your sister
under my protection here.

277
00:16:01,201 --> 00:16:02,911
If anything happens to her,
anything at all...

278
00:16:02,995 --> 00:16:05,873
I swear to you
I will get very choked up.

279
00:16:05,956 --> 00:16:07,958
Honestly.
There could be tears.

280
00:16:16,592 --> 00:16:20,804
Don't mind
the Captain none, Simon.
I know he'll look out for her.

281
00:16:21,430 --> 00:16:23,640
They'll be back
before you can spit.

282
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:28,770
Well, not that you spit.

283
00:16:34,234 --> 00:16:35,986
(Jayne)
What are we hoping
to find here...

284
00:16:36,069 --> 00:16:37,487
that equals
the worth of a turd?

285
00:16:37,571 --> 00:16:40,407
(Mal)
Security payroll. Alliance
don't have the manpower...

286
00:16:40,449 --> 00:16:43,035
to "enforce the peace"
on every outer-rim planet.

287
00:16:43,118 --> 00:16:46,371
They hire
out to the private firms,
who will not work for credit.

288
00:16:46,455 --> 00:16:49,917
They get paid in cashy money,
which once a month rests here.

289
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:52,002
Don't that lead back to
the Alliance, anyhow?

290
00:16:52,085 --> 00:16:54,922
No private firm
would ever report the theft
of their own payroll.

291
00:16:55,005 --> 00:16:58,175
They'd appear weak,
might lose their contract.

292
00:16:58,258 --> 00:17:01,887
Yeah, we're as ghosts in this.
Won't but rattle the floor.

293
00:17:01,929 --> 00:17:06,099
Shiny. Let's be bad guys.

294
00:17:06,225 --> 00:17:09,228
Hands and knees and heads
bowed down! Everybody, down!

295
00:17:09,311 --> 00:17:10,479
[Woman screaming]

296
00:17:11,563 --> 00:17:12,522
[Grunting]

297
00:17:18,946 --> 00:17:21,031
Looks like this is the place.

298
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:24,785
You all wanna
be looking very intently
at your own belly buttons.

299
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:28,121
I see a head start to rise,
violence is going to ensue.

300
00:17:29,122 --> 00:17:31,250
Probably guessed we mean
to be thieving here...

301
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:33,460
but what we're after
is not yours.

302
00:17:34,211 --> 00:17:36,213
So let's have
no undue fussing.

303
00:17:36,964 --> 00:17:38,257
She's locked up.

304
00:17:52,688 --> 00:17:54,815
[People murmuring]

305
00:18:25,053 --> 00:18:27,514
Do you know what
the definition of a hero is?

306
00:18:28,223 --> 00:18:30,434
Someone who gets
other people killed.

307
00:18:30,726 --> 00:18:32,436
You can look it up later.

308
00:18:35,731 --> 00:18:37,649
Big happy family.

309
00:18:42,988 --> 00:18:43,989
[Beeping]

310
00:18:47,034 --> 00:18:50,537
At last.
We can retire and give up
this life of crime.

311
00:18:55,417 --> 00:18:56,752
[Metal rattling]

312
00:18:57,127 --> 00:18:58,086
Hey!

313
00:18:59,755 --> 00:19:02,591
You all are Browncoats, eh?
Fought for independence?

314
00:19:02,674 --> 00:19:04,718
Petty thieving
ain't exactly soldiers' work.

315
00:19:04,801 --> 00:19:09,097
War's long done.
We're all just folk now.
Listen up!

316
00:19:09,848 --> 00:19:11,516
We are coming down
to empty that vault!

317
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:14,478
(guard)
You have to give me
your authorization password!

318
00:19:18,523 --> 00:19:19,608
(guard)
Okay.

319
00:19:33,497 --> 00:19:35,832
I'm telling you I heard it.
Repeater.

320
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:40,170
Did sound somewhat
like gun blast. Maybe
you ought run tell Lawman.

321
00:19:41,004 --> 00:19:42,005
[Screaming]

322
00:19:43,006 --> 00:19:45,676
What the hell is up?
You all right?

323
00:19:46,468 --> 00:19:48,136
What's going on?

324
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,806
Reavers.

325
00:19:57,521 --> 00:20:01,149
The leg is good. It'll bleed
plenty and we avoid
any necessary organs.

326
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:02,609
I was thinking
more of a graze.

327
00:20:02,693 --> 00:20:04,528
No, you don't want it
to look like you gave up.

328
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:05,779
No, I get that.

329
00:20:05,863 --> 00:20:07,197
(Jayne)
Mal!

330
00:20:07,322 --> 00:20:09,575
Every heist, he's got
to start yelling my name.

331
00:20:09,658 --> 00:20:12,536
Mal! Reavers!

332
00:20:12,870 --> 00:20:15,497
The girl's pitching a fit.
They're here
or they're coming soon.

333
00:20:15,539 --> 00:20:16,957
Get on the Mule.

334
00:20:17,541 --> 00:20:19,835
Does that lock
from the inside?
Yes.

335
00:20:19,877 --> 00:20:22,379
Get everyone upstairs.
You get them down here
and you seal it.

336
00:20:22,462 --> 00:20:25,007
As long as you got air
you don't open up,
you understand?

337
00:20:25,090 --> 00:20:28,176
Get them inside the vault!

338
00:20:28,427 --> 00:20:31,430
You see them?
Zoe, take the wheel!

339
00:20:31,513 --> 00:20:32,890
(Jayne)
Anybody see them?

340
00:20:39,354 --> 00:20:40,564
Take me with you!

341
00:20:40,647 --> 00:20:42,316
Get back in the vault with
the others.

342
00:20:42,399 --> 00:20:45,319
I can't stay here! Please!
It's too many. Move ahead.

343
00:20:45,402 --> 00:20:46,820
Please!

344
00:20:53,493 --> 00:20:54,578
[Screaming]

345
00:21:00,918 --> 00:21:03,253
[Engine revving]

346
00:21:21,396 --> 00:21:23,857
Faster! Faster!
Faster would be better!

347
00:21:32,824 --> 00:21:34,535
How come
they ain't blowing us
out the air?

348
00:21:34,576 --> 00:21:37,454
They wanna run us down.
The up-close kill.

349
00:21:39,081 --> 00:21:41,291
They want us alive
when they eat us.

350
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:45,712
Boy, sure would be nice
if we had some grenades,
don't you think?

351
00:21:45,879 --> 00:21:47,172
[Gun firing]

352
00:21:47,256 --> 00:21:50,384
Wash, baby, can you hear me?
We're moments from air.

353
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:52,761
You got somebody
behind you?
Reavers.

354
00:21:55,097 --> 00:21:56,098
Kaylee!

355
00:21:56,181 --> 00:21:57,975
Heat her up. We got Reavers.

356
00:22:02,062 --> 00:22:05,107
We're not gonna
get to you in time.
Keep moving, honey.

357
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:06,775
We're coming to you.

358
00:22:14,283 --> 00:22:16,493
(Jayne)
Where's my clips?
(Mal)

359
00:22:16,952 --> 00:22:17,953
[Screaming]

360
00:22:25,752 --> 00:22:26,879
[Groaning]

361
00:22:28,463 --> 00:22:29,923
[Jayne yelling]

362
00:22:32,134 --> 00:22:33,468
I won't get ate!

363
00:22:34,803 --> 00:22:39,224
You shoot me if they take me!
Well, don't shoot me first!

364
00:22:52,779 --> 00:22:54,114
[Grunting]

365
00:22:58,035 --> 00:23:00,037
Get some distance on them.

366
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:02,915
You come to the flats,
I want you to swing round.

367
00:23:03,290 --> 00:23:05,209
We're gonna try
a Barn Swallow.

368
00:23:05,292 --> 00:23:07,211
Simon! Open her up!

369
00:23:12,341 --> 00:23:13,800
(Mal)
They're closing on us!

370
00:23:13,884 --> 00:23:16,094
Those rocks,
give them a taste.

371
00:23:31,652 --> 00:23:34,029
(Wash)
Okay, baby,
we talked this through.

372
00:23:37,324 --> 00:23:38,909
Talking ain't doing.

373
00:23:38,992 --> 00:23:40,077
[Speaking Chinese]

374
00:23:41,078 --> 00:23:42,079
[Whooshing]

375
00:24:15,571 --> 00:24:16,572
[Grunting]

376
00:24:18,115 --> 00:24:19,157
[Groaning]

377
00:24:19,199 --> 00:24:22,661
River?
I swallowed a bug.

378
00:24:27,124 --> 00:24:30,627
Are you okay?
Is he okay?

379
00:24:30,711 --> 00:24:31,670
[Screeching]

380
00:24:43,932 --> 00:24:46,310
(Wash)
We all here? What's going on?

381
00:24:46,602 --> 00:24:47,895
Hello?

382
00:24:50,397 --> 00:24:51,690
No casualties.

383
00:24:51,982 --> 00:24:54,484
Anybody following?
(Wash)
Nice flying, baby.

384
00:24:54,568 --> 00:24:56,987
That's a negative.
Clean getaway.

385
00:24:57,404 --> 00:25:01,700
Set course for Beaumonde.
First thing,
I want this body...

386
00:25:01,783 --> 00:25:02,784
(Kaylee)
Simon!

387
00:25:03,952 --> 00:25:05,662
[Speaking Chinese]

388
00:25:05,787 --> 00:25:07,539
You son of a whore.
I'm a hair's breadth...

389
00:25:07,623 --> 00:25:08,957
from riddling
you with holes, Doctor.

390
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:12,502
One simple job!
She'll be fine!
She is fine!

391
00:25:12,544 --> 00:25:14,671
Except for being still crazy,
she's a picture of health!

392
00:25:14,755 --> 00:25:18,467
Wasn't for River,
we'd probably be left there.
She felt them coming.

393
00:25:18,634 --> 00:25:20,719
(Simon)
Never again.
You understand me?

394
00:25:20,802 --> 00:25:23,597
Seems I remember a talk about
you giving orders on my boat.

395
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,224
Well, we're off your boat.

396
00:25:25,307 --> 00:25:27,768
Just as soon as River
gets her share of the bounty.

397
00:25:27,851 --> 00:25:30,604
Let's not do anything hasty...
No, shiny!

398
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:32,481
We'll be on Beaumonde
in 10 hours' time...

399
00:25:32,564 --> 00:25:35,400
you can pick up your earnings
and be on your merry.

400
00:25:35,692 --> 00:25:38,529
Meantime, you do your job.

401
00:25:39,404 --> 00:25:40,989
Patch up my crew.

402
00:25:43,325 --> 00:25:44,952
He didn't lie down.

403
00:25:46,745 --> 00:25:48,372
They never lie down.

404
00:25:57,172 --> 00:25:59,591
(Zoe)
No, I think things will glide
a deal smoother for us...

405
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:01,593
without River
and Simon on board...

406
00:26:01,677 --> 00:26:03,095
but how long
do you think they'll last?

407
00:26:03,136 --> 00:26:04,721
Doc made his call.

408
00:26:04,763 --> 00:26:05,764
Yeah.

409
00:26:05,847 --> 00:26:07,683
They's as babes in a basket
when we took them in.

410
00:26:07,766 --> 00:26:09,560
We sheltered them plenty.

411
00:26:09,643 --> 00:26:12,980
Man has to cut loose,
learn to stand on his own.

412
00:26:14,857 --> 00:26:16,650
Like that man back in town?

413
00:26:19,653 --> 00:26:21,071
I had to shoot him.

414
00:26:21,113 --> 00:26:23,115
What Reavers would've done
before they killed him...

415
00:26:23,198 --> 00:26:25,701
I know.
That was a piece of mercy.

416
00:26:26,535 --> 00:26:29,496
But before that,
him begging us
to bring him along.

417
00:26:30,664 --> 00:26:33,625
We couldn't take the weight.
Would've slowed us down.

418
00:26:33,667 --> 00:26:36,920
You know that for certain?
Mule won't run with five.

419
00:26:37,629 --> 00:26:41,341
I should've dumped the girl?
Or you? Or Jayne?

420
00:26:41,508 --> 00:26:42,801
Oh, Jayne...

421
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:46,597
You could've
tossed the payload.
Tossed the...

422
00:26:47,806 --> 00:26:51,560
Zoe, I got bits falling
off my ship, I got
a crew ain't been paid...

423
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:54,605
and, oh, yeah, a powerful need
to eat sometime this month.

424
00:26:55,022 --> 00:26:56,732
We tell Fanty and Mingo
we skunked the job...

425
00:26:56,773 --> 00:26:58,775
what do think
they'll do to us?

426
00:27:00,652 --> 00:27:02,571
We're close to gone out here.

427
00:27:03,739 --> 00:27:06,158
We get a job,
we got to make good.

428
00:27:06,742 --> 00:27:09,369
Sir, I don't disagree
on any particular point.

429
00:27:11,121 --> 00:27:12,289
It's just...

430
00:27:15,459 --> 00:27:18,712
in the time of war,
we would've never
left a man stranded.

431
00:27:20,130 --> 00:27:21,840
Maybe that's why we lost.

432
00:27:31,225 --> 00:27:32,893
That was close.

433
00:27:35,229 --> 00:27:36,605
(Jayne)
I do not get it.

434
00:27:37,481 --> 00:27:39,274
How's a guy get so wrong?

435
00:27:39,358 --> 00:27:42,819
Cutting on his own face,
raping and murdering.

436
00:27:45,739 --> 00:27:47,741
I'll kill a man
in a fair fight...

437
00:27:48,534 --> 00:27:51,078
or if I think
he's gonna
start a fair fight...

438
00:27:51,912 --> 00:27:55,457
or if he bothers me,
or if there's a woman...

439
00:27:55,874 --> 00:28:00,712
or if I'm getting paid.
Mostly only when
I'm getting paid.

440
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:04,591
These Reavers,
the last 10 years...

441
00:28:04,675 --> 00:28:07,511
they show up like
the boogeyman from stories.

442
00:28:08,512 --> 00:28:11,807
Eating people alive?
Where does that get fun?

443
00:28:13,392 --> 00:28:15,727
Shepherd Book said
they was men who just...

444
00:28:15,811 --> 00:28:19,147
reached the edge of space,
saw a vasty nothingness...

445
00:28:19,231 --> 00:28:21,233
and went
bibbledy over it.

446
00:28:21,358 --> 00:28:22,359
Oh, hell.

447
00:28:24,152 --> 00:28:25,696
I've been to the edge.

448
00:28:26,405 --> 00:28:30,284
Just looked like more space.

449
00:28:31,285 --> 00:28:32,661
I don't know.

450
00:28:32,744 --> 00:28:35,122
It can get awful lonely
in the black.

451
00:28:36,373 --> 00:28:39,877
Like to get addlepated
ourselves, we stay
on this boat much longer.

452
00:28:40,669 --> 00:28:43,130
Captain will drive
us all off, one by one.

453
00:28:43,797 --> 00:28:45,799
Just like Simon and River.

454
00:28:47,551 --> 00:28:49,011
Just like Inara.

455
00:28:50,304 --> 00:28:53,181
Kaylee, are you ever going
to put that capture down?

456
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:55,809
(Kaylee)
We got to have records
of everything, Inara.

457
00:28:55,851 --> 00:28:59,730
A bona fide companion
entertained clients
on this very ship.

458
00:29:00,272 --> 00:29:03,650
In this very bed.
Well, I can't do my work here.

459
00:29:03,692 --> 00:29:05,736
And I don't think
the Captain approves.

460
00:29:05,819 --> 00:29:07,404
The Captain
wants you to stay...

461
00:29:07,487 --> 00:29:10,866
That man doesn't
know what he wants.
I don't have time to...

462
00:29:26,381 --> 00:29:29,760
~~[music playing]

463
00:29:39,353 --> 00:29:41,522
[People chattering]

464
00:29:45,025 --> 00:29:47,528
(woman)
Don't talk to the barkers,
talk to the captains.

465
00:29:47,611 --> 00:29:51,031
You look the captain
in the eye.
Know who you're dealing with.

466
00:29:51,573 --> 00:29:53,116
I wish there was...

467
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:58,789
You shouldn't
ought to be so clean.

468
00:29:59,248 --> 00:30:02,709
It's a dead giveaway
you don't belong,
you always got to be tidy.

469
00:30:02,793 --> 00:30:04,753
Don't pay anybody in advance.

470
00:30:06,421 --> 00:30:08,882
And don't ride in anything
with a Capissen 38 engine...

471
00:30:08,966 --> 00:30:10,968
they fall right
out of the sky.

472
00:30:11,635 --> 00:30:13,011
Kaylee.

473
00:30:24,439 --> 00:30:26,608
River, do you want
to stay with them?

474
00:30:28,277 --> 00:30:29,820
It isn't safe.

475
00:30:31,572 --> 00:30:32,531
No.

476
00:30:34,867 --> 00:30:36,952
I fear it isn't safe anymore.

477
00:30:39,454 --> 00:30:40,664
For them.

478
00:30:43,083 --> 00:30:45,377
[People clamoring]

479
00:30:58,348 --> 00:31:00,601
(man on TV)
...only survivors
of the massacre apparently...

480
00:31:00,684 --> 00:31:03,437
Iocked themselves in
the train station vault.

481
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:06,523
Kaylee,
this is a place of business.
We can talk about Simon when...

482
00:31:06,607 --> 00:31:08,066
When he's
four worlds away?

483
00:31:08,108 --> 00:31:10,444
Or the Alliance gets a hold
of him and River?

484
00:31:10,527 --> 00:31:11,570
(Mal)
That ain't my worry.

485
00:31:11,653 --> 00:31:13,947
I got to finish this job
and get us another one.

486
00:31:14,031 --> 00:31:15,866
Can't do that
carrying those two.

487
00:31:16,283 --> 00:31:18,160
(Kaylee)
How can you be so cold?

488
00:31:18,243 --> 00:31:20,412
Captain didn't
make them fugitives.

489
00:31:20,495 --> 00:31:22,664
But he could
have made them family.

490
00:31:22,831 --> 00:31:25,626
Instead of keeping Simon
from seeing I was there.

491
00:31:26,376 --> 00:31:29,296
When I carried such a torch,
