741
00:48:44,748 --> 00:48:46,458
Got some of your
stuff in a trunk.

742
00:48:46,542 --> 00:48:48,085
I never did get a chance
to drop it off.

743
00:48:48,126 --> 00:48:52,422
I didn't mean to leave stuff.
I didn't look
through the stuff.

744
00:48:52,798 --> 00:48:55,926
I just...
Just sundries I expect.

745
00:48:58,845 --> 00:49:01,640
So I'll send you a wave,
soon as I can.

746
00:49:02,391 --> 00:49:03,559
Thank you.

747
00:49:12,484 --> 00:49:15,362
Inara, nice to see
her again.

748
00:49:17,322 --> 00:49:19,700
So, trap?
Trap.

749
00:49:20,242 --> 00:49:22,911
We going in?
Only but a few hours out.

750
00:49:23,495 --> 00:49:26,498
Yeah, but, remember the part
where it's a trap?

751
00:49:26,707 --> 00:49:29,126
If that's the case,
then Inara's already
caught in it.

752
00:49:29,209 --> 00:49:31,211
She wouldn't
set us up willing.

753
00:49:31,461 --> 00:49:34,298
Might be we got a shot
at seeing who's
turning these wheels.

754
00:49:34,381 --> 00:49:35,424
We go in.

755
00:49:35,465 --> 00:49:38,802
But how can you be sure
Inara don't just
wanna see you?

756
00:49:39,761 --> 00:49:42,139
Sometimes people
have feelings.

757
00:49:42,306 --> 00:49:44,349
I'm referring here to people.

758
00:49:46,143 --> 00:49:48,228
You all were watching,
I take it.

759
00:49:50,147 --> 00:49:51,899
Yes.
Did you see us fight?

760
00:49:52,149 --> 00:49:53,692
No.
Trap.

761
00:50:01,658 --> 00:50:05,495
We're about 70 miles
from the Training House,
and nobody on radar.

762
00:50:05,579 --> 00:50:08,040
If the Alliance is about,
they're laying low.

763
00:50:08,123 --> 00:50:09,291
They're about.

764
00:50:09,333 --> 00:50:11,376
Find us a home.
I'll take the shuttle
a little closer.

765
00:50:11,460 --> 00:50:13,128
Zoe, ship is yours.

766
00:50:13,170 --> 00:50:15,714
Remember. If anything
happens to me...

767
00:50:15,797 --> 00:50:17,507
or if you don't hear from me
within the hour...

768
00:50:17,591 --> 00:50:19,843
you take this ship
and you come
and you rescue me.

769
00:50:19,927 --> 00:50:20,928
What?

770
00:50:21,553 --> 00:50:23,847
Risk my ship?
I mean it.

771
00:50:24,306 --> 00:50:27,017
It's cold out there.
And I don't wanna get left.

772
00:50:43,867 --> 00:50:47,246
Dear Buddha,
please bring me a pony,
and a plastic rocket, and...

773
00:50:47,329 --> 00:50:49,206
Mal! What are you
doing here?

774
00:50:49,831 --> 00:50:50,999
Well, you invited me.

775
00:50:51,083 --> 00:50:53,669
I never thought for a second
you'd be stupid enough
to come.

776
00:50:53,710 --> 00:50:55,587
Well, that makes you
kind of a tease, doesn't it?

777
00:50:55,671 --> 00:50:57,589
You knew my invitation
wasn't on the level.

778
00:50:57,673 --> 00:51:00,634
Which led me to conclude
that you must be
in some trouble.

779
00:51:00,717 --> 00:51:02,469
I'm fine. I'm giddy.

780
00:51:02,553 --> 00:51:04,972
For a woman schooled
in telling a man
what he wants to hear...

781
00:51:05,055 --> 00:51:08,517
you ain't much of a liar.
Mal, you cannot
handle this man.

782
00:51:14,606 --> 00:51:15,774
I have to say, Captain...

783
00:51:15,858 --> 00:51:18,694
I'm impressed that you
would come for her yourself.

784
00:51:19,027 --> 00:51:22,155
And that you would make it
this far, in that outfit.

785
00:51:23,323 --> 00:51:25,617
I can be very graceful
when I need to.

786
00:51:25,701 --> 00:51:27,035
I've no doubt.

787
00:51:28,453 --> 00:51:31,164
What are you doing?
I'm praying for you, Mal.

788
00:51:31,874 --> 00:51:33,667
She's very thoughtful.

789
00:51:34,084 --> 00:51:37,045
But I mean it when I say
I've no intent to harm you.

790
00:51:37,838 --> 00:51:39,464
Speak your piece.

791
00:51:39,923 --> 00:51:41,800
I think you're
beginning to understand...

792
00:51:41,884 --> 00:51:43,844
how dangerous River Tam is.

793
00:51:44,219 --> 00:51:46,013
She is a mite unpredictable.

794
00:51:46,263 --> 00:51:48,182
Mood swings, of a sort.

795
00:51:48,223 --> 00:51:50,767
It's worse than you know.
It usually is.

796
00:51:50,851 --> 00:51:54,479
That girl will
rain destruction down
on you and your ship.

797
00:51:55,898 --> 00:51:58,650
She is an albatross, Captain.

798
00:51:58,817 --> 00:52:00,527
Way I remember it...

799
00:52:00,652 --> 00:52:03,989
albatross was
a ship's good luck,
till some idiot killed it.

800
00:52:04,531 --> 00:52:07,201
Yes, I've read a poem.
Try not to faint.

801
00:52:07,743 --> 00:52:09,578
I've seen your war record.

802
00:52:10,579 --> 00:52:13,123
I know how you must feel about
the Alliance.

803
00:52:13,415 --> 00:52:15,584
You really don't.
Fair to say.

804
00:52:16,335 --> 00:52:19,171
But I have to hope
you understand,
you can't beat us.

805
00:52:19,254 --> 00:52:20,964
I got no need to beat you.

806
00:52:21,048 --> 00:52:23,926
I just want to go my way.
And you can do that...

807
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:27,763
once you let me take
River Tam back home.

808
00:52:31,475 --> 00:52:34,019
No, no. You're working
this deal all crabbed.

809
00:52:34,102 --> 00:52:36,813
You got to open with payment.
That is a trap.

810
00:52:36,939 --> 00:52:40,526
I offer money,
you'll play the man of honor
and take umbrage.

811
00:52:40,734 --> 00:52:43,362
I ask you to do what is right,
you'll play the brigand.

812
00:52:43,445 --> 00:52:45,948
I have no stomach for games.

813
00:52:46,448 --> 00:52:48,450
I already know
you will not see reason.

814
00:52:48,534 --> 00:52:50,077
The Alliance wanted to
show me a reason...

815
00:52:50,160 --> 00:52:52,371
they shouldn't have sent
an assassin.

816
00:52:58,585 --> 00:53:01,713
I have a warship
in deep orbit, Captain.

817
00:53:02,381 --> 00:53:05,884
We locked on
to Serenity's pulse beacon
the moment you hit atmo.

818
00:53:06,051 --> 00:53:08,053
I can speak a word
and send a missile...

819
00:53:08,136 --> 00:53:10,848
to that exact location
inside of three minutes.

820
00:53:10,931 --> 00:53:12,099
You do that...

821
00:53:13,183 --> 00:53:16,061
you'd best make peace
with your dear
and fluffy lord.

822
00:53:19,815 --> 00:53:21,066
Pulse beacon.

823
00:53:21,316 --> 00:53:25,279
Advice from an old tracker.
You want to find someone,
use your eyes.

824
00:53:25,821 --> 00:53:28,115
How long do you think
you can really run from us?

825
00:53:28,156 --> 00:53:30,784
I never credited
the Alliance with
an overabundance of brains.

826
00:53:30,868 --> 00:53:33,036
And if you're
the best they got...
Captain Reynolds...

827
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:35,914
I should tell you,
so that you don't
waste your time...

828
00:53:35,956 --> 00:53:39,918
you can't make me angry.
Please, spend
an hour with him.

829
00:53:40,711 --> 00:53:43,463
I want to resolve this
like civilized men.

830
00:53:44,548 --> 00:53:46,466
I'm not threatening you.

831
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:48,302
I'm unarmed.
Good.

832
00:53:48,343 --> 00:53:49,553
[Gun firing]

833
00:53:53,390 --> 00:53:55,434
I am, of course,
wearing full body armor.

834
00:53:55,517 --> 00:53:57,853
I am not a moron.
(lnara)
Wait, just let...

835
00:53:57,936 --> 00:53:59,438
[all grunting]

836
00:54:07,154 --> 00:54:08,113
[Groans]

837
00:54:14,703 --> 00:54:15,996
[Glass shattering]

838
00:54:16,079 --> 00:54:17,497
[Groaning]

839
00:54:21,210 --> 00:54:22,211
[Panting]

840
00:54:23,587 --> 00:54:24,838
[Gasping]

841
00:54:26,048 --> 00:54:27,549
What, no backup?

842
00:54:28,050 --> 00:54:31,261
Making an awful ruckus.
They'll come
when they're needed.

843
00:54:31,345 --> 00:54:32,763
I'd start whistling.

844
00:54:32,888 --> 00:54:36,058
Captain, what do you think
is going to happen here?

845
00:54:38,852 --> 00:54:40,479
[Both grunting]

846
00:55:00,499 --> 00:55:01,959
[Lnara groans]

847
00:55:05,671 --> 00:55:06,964
[Groans]

848
00:55:11,927 --> 00:55:13,428
[Glass shatters]

849
00:55:20,727 --> 00:55:22,145
[Panting]

850
00:55:22,896 --> 00:55:27,192
Nothing here is what it seems.
He isn't the plucky hero.

851
00:55:28,026 --> 00:55:31,989
The Alliance isn't
some evil empire.
This is not the grand arena.

852
00:55:32,239 --> 00:55:33,866
And that's not incense.

853
00:55:37,494 --> 00:55:39,496
[Beeping]

854
00:55:40,873 --> 00:55:42,082
Sir, can you hear me?

855
00:55:42,165 --> 00:55:44,668
Just a flash bomb. Go. Go!

856
00:55:45,377 --> 00:55:47,504
[Lnara and Mal grunting]

857
00:55:50,382 --> 00:55:53,635
What have you done
to my shuttle?
It's not your shuttle.

858
00:55:54,011 --> 00:55:55,888
Head east. Keep her low.

859
00:55:56,054 --> 00:55:57,639
[Engine revving]

860
00:56:11,737 --> 00:56:13,530
Okay, forget
the pulse beacon.

861
00:56:13,572 --> 00:56:15,741
There must be another way
to track the ship.

862
00:56:15,824 --> 00:56:17,242
Get a read
on the nav. Sat.

863
00:56:17,284 --> 00:56:19,870
It's a registered transport,
you must be able to locate.

864
00:56:19,912 --> 00:56:20,913
(ensign)
Sir?

865
00:56:20,996 --> 00:56:22,873
Yes, have you found
a nav. Sat. Trajectory?

866
00:56:22,915 --> 00:56:25,375
Sir, we found seven.

867
00:56:33,091 --> 00:56:34,843
(Inara)
We've every reason
to be afraid.

868
00:56:35,260 --> 00:56:38,222
Why, 'cause this guy
beat up Mal?
That ain't so hard.

869
00:56:38,305 --> 00:56:40,849
He didn't beat me up.
Nobody said that.

870
00:56:40,933 --> 00:56:42,684
Because he's a believer.

871
00:56:42,935 --> 00:56:47,356
He's intelligent, methodical,
and devout in his belief...

872
00:56:47,439 --> 00:56:49,816
that killing River
is the right thing to do.

873
00:56:49,900 --> 00:56:52,444
So no hope
of a reward, huh?

874
00:56:53,403 --> 00:56:56,823
Did he say anything
about a Miranda?

875
00:56:57,616 --> 00:56:58,700
What is that?

876
00:56:58,784 --> 00:57:01,161
Don't know who or what,
but it's on River's mind.

877
00:57:01,245 --> 00:57:03,205
Conjure it might be the reason
they're after her.

878
00:57:03,288 --> 00:57:06,208
You think maybe it poses
some kind of threat
to the Alliance?

879
00:57:06,250 --> 00:57:07,626
Do we care?

880
00:57:08,043 --> 00:57:09,753
Are we caring about that?

881
00:57:09,795 --> 00:57:12,464
You dumb-ass hogs,
the only people
she's a threat to is...

882
00:57:12,548 --> 00:57:14,049
us on this boat.

883
00:57:14,091 --> 00:57:15,926
Look, we get back
to Haven...

884
00:57:16,009 --> 00:57:17,052
in a few
hours' time.
Oh, yeah.

885
00:57:17,094 --> 00:57:18,428
Hiding under
the Shepherd's skirts...

886
00:57:18,470 --> 00:57:19,513
that's a manful scheme.

887
00:57:19,596 --> 00:57:21,598
You wanna run this ship?
Yes.

888
00:57:22,683 --> 00:57:24,476
Well, you can't.

889
00:57:25,227 --> 00:57:27,396
Do a damn sight
better job than you.

890
00:57:27,521 --> 00:57:29,940
Getting us lashed over
a couple of strays.

891
00:57:30,190 --> 00:57:32,192
No offense, Doc.
I think it's
noble as a grape...

892
00:57:32,276 --> 00:57:33,485
the way you look to River.

893
00:57:33,569 --> 00:57:36,029
But she ain't my sister
and she ain't your crew.

894
00:57:36,113 --> 00:57:38,448
Oh, and neither is she
exactly helpless.

895
00:57:38,824 --> 00:57:41,368
So, where's it writ
that we got to lay down
our lives for her?

896
00:57:41,451 --> 00:57:42,995
Which is what you've
steered us toward.

897
00:57:43,078 --> 00:57:44,788
I didn't start this.

898
00:57:45,414 --> 00:57:46,957
No, that's right.

899
00:57:47,791 --> 00:57:51,461
Alliance starts the war,
and then you volunteer.

900
00:57:53,422 --> 00:57:55,090
Battle of Serenity, Mal.

901
00:57:55,173 --> 00:57:58,427
Besides Zoe here, how many...
Hey, I'm talking at you.

902
00:58:02,472 --> 00:58:05,475
How many men in your platoon
came out of there alive?

903
00:58:08,729 --> 00:58:10,856
You wanna leave this room.

904
00:58:13,692 --> 00:58:15,444
Damn right, I do.

905
00:58:22,784 --> 00:58:24,786
This isn't
the war, Mal.

906
00:58:25,662 --> 00:58:27,915
You telling me that
'cause you think I don't know?

907
00:58:27,998 --> 00:58:30,125
You came to the Training House
looking for a fight.

908
00:58:30,167 --> 00:58:32,085
I came looking for you.

909
00:58:33,378 --> 00:58:35,839
I just want to know
who I'm dealing with.

910
00:58:35,964 --> 00:58:38,592
I've seen too many versions
of you to be sure.

911
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:43,096
I start fighting a war,
I guarantee
you'll see something new.

912
00:58:50,270 --> 00:58:51,480
We'll get off.

913
00:58:51,563 --> 00:58:53,190
River and I will
get off at Haven.

914
00:58:53,273 --> 00:58:55,025
We'll find some...
Nobody's saying that.

915
00:58:55,108 --> 00:58:56,944
Nobody besides Jayne
is saying that.

916
00:58:56,985 --> 00:58:57,986
Mal.

917
00:59:00,489 --> 00:59:03,575
I got no answers
for you, Inara.
I got no rudder.

918
00:59:03,659 --> 00:59:06,620
Wind blows northerly,
I go north.
That's who I am.

919
00:59:06,662 --> 00:59:09,248
Now, maybe that ain't
a man to lead,
but they have to follow.

920
00:59:09,331 --> 00:59:10,415
So you wanna tear me down...

921
00:59:10,499 --> 00:59:12,626
do it inside your own mind.
I'm not trying
to tear you down.

922
00:59:12,709 --> 00:59:14,294
But you fog things up.

923
00:59:15,128 --> 00:59:16,797
You always have.

924
00:59:18,465 --> 00:59:19,883
You spin me about.

925
00:59:23,095 --> 00:59:25,264
I wish like hell
you was elsewhere.

926
00:59:27,474 --> 00:59:28,559
I was.

927
01:00:02,885 --> 01:00:04,178
[Rumbling]

928
01:00:19,443 --> 01:00:21,528
[Flies buzzing]

929
01:00:24,156 --> 01:00:25,324
[Gasps]

930
01:00:49,181 --> 01:00:50,390
[Speaking Chinese]

931
01:00:59,525 --> 01:01:00,901
[Beeping]

932
01:01:01,693 --> 01:01:03,946
No trouble,
little crazy person.

933
01:01:05,948 --> 01:01:09,326
We're going
for a nice shuttle ride.

934
01:01:12,955 --> 01:01:14,164
[Gun fires]

935
01:01:22,005 --> 01:01:23,924
[Doorknob rattling]

936
01:01:26,844 --> 01:01:28,637
She's out. Jayne's down.

937
01:01:28,846 --> 01:01:31,390
The other way.
Find her and do not engage.

938
01:01:36,103 --> 01:01:37,563
[Beeping]

939
01:01:53,829 --> 01:01:55,289
It's gonna be okay...

940
01:01:57,457 --> 01:01:58,458
[coughs]

941
01:02:05,883 --> 01:02:08,051
She's sealed off the bridge.
I do not like her there.

942
01:02:08,135 --> 01:02:09,803
Check the shuttle.
She could have snuck in.

943
01:02:09,887 --> 01:02:10,888
Captain.

944
01:02:44,087 --> 01:02:45,714
[Computer beeps]

945
01:02:56,934 --> 01:02:59,853
The government's man,
he says you're a danger to us.

946
01:03:00,854 --> 01:03:02,481
Not worth helping.

947
01:03:05,067 --> 01:03:06,235
Is he right?

948
01:03:07,569 --> 01:03:09,988
Are you anything but a weapon?

949
01:03:13,158 --> 01:03:16,245
I've staked my crew's life on
the theory you're a person...

950
01:03:16,328 --> 01:03:19,540
actual and whole,
and if I'm wrong,
you'd best shoot me now.

951
01:03:19,581 --> 01:03:20,582
[Clicks]

952
01:03:20,749 --> 01:03:22,626
Or we could talk more.

953
01:03:33,679 --> 01:03:34,763
Miranda.

954
01:03:38,892 --> 01:03:41,270
How can it be there's
a whole planet
called Miranda...

955
01:03:41,353 --> 01:03:42,604
and none of us knowed that?

956
01:03:42,688 --> 01:03:46,066
Because there isn't one.
It's a blackrock.
Uninhabitable.

957
01:03:46,567 --> 01:03:49,611
Terraforming didn't hold,
or some such.
Few settlers died.

958
01:03:49,695 --> 01:03:51,196
(Zoe)
Was it right before the war?

959
01:03:51,280 --> 01:03:55,158
I had to show them.
I didn't know if you were
going to make me sleep.

960
01:03:56,869 --> 01:03:58,954
You could have asked.
(Kaylee)
Wait a tick, yeah.

961
01:03:59,037 --> 01:04:02,708
Some years back,
there was call for workers
to settle on Miranda.

962
01:04:02,749 --> 01:04:04,543
Daddy talked about it.
Nothing about it...

963
01:04:04,585 --> 01:04:06,628
on the Cortex.
History, Astronomy,
it's not in there.

964
01:04:06,712 --> 01:04:09,047
Half of writing history
is hiding the truth.

965
01:04:09,089 --> 01:04:12,050
There's something
on that rock the Alliance
doesn't want known.

966
01:04:12,092 --> 01:04:14,303
That's right at the edge
of the Burnham Quadrant,
right?

967
01:04:14,386 --> 01:04:16,722
Furthest planet out?
It's not that far from here.

968
01:04:16,763 --> 01:04:18,515
Whoa. No. No. Honey...
That's a bad notion.

969
01:04:18,599 --> 01:04:20,934
...you show them the bad.
I got it, baby.

970
01:04:24,605 --> 01:04:27,232
(Zoe)
This is us, at Haven,
and here's Miranda.

971
01:04:27,816 --> 01:04:32,029
All along here,
that empty space in between,
that's Reaver territory.

972
01:04:32,112 --> 01:04:34,781
They just float out there,
sending out raiding parties.

973
01:04:34,865 --> 01:04:37,159
Nobody ventures there.
Not even the Alliance.

974
01:04:37,242 --> 01:04:39,494
You go through that,
you're signing up
to be a banquet.

975
01:04:39,578 --> 01:04:42,206
I'm on board with our standard
run-and-hide scenario.

976
01:04:42,289 --> 01:04:43,999
And we are just about...

977
01:04:44,791 --> 01:04:45,751
Wait.

978
01:05:03,143 --> 01:05:05,270
(Jayne)
Doesn't look like Reavers.
Wasn't.

979
01:05:11,109 --> 01:05:12,110
(Kaylee)
Shepherd?

980
01:05:13,946 --> 01:05:15,072
Shepherd?

981
01:05:16,406 --> 01:05:17,658
(Kaylee)
Shepherd Book?

982
01:05:35,801 --> 01:05:36,760
[Cocking gun]

983
01:05:36,844 --> 01:05:37,845
[Man coughing]

984
01:05:38,720 --> 01:05:40,138
Get the Doc.

985
01:05:41,598 --> 01:05:42,599
Shepherd.

986
01:05:42,641 --> 01:05:43,642
[Gasping]

987
01:05:43,767 --> 01:05:46,645
Don't move.
Won't go far.

988
01:05:49,147 --> 01:05:51,108
Shouldn't have been you.

989
01:05:51,942 --> 01:05:54,570
Alliance should've hit us.
Should've hit me.

990
01:05:55,946 --> 01:05:57,656
That crossed my mind.

991
01:06:02,202 --> 01:06:05,330
I shot him down.
Yeah. I see.

992
01:06:05,581 --> 01:06:08,125
I killed the ship
that killed us.

993
01:06:09,877 --> 01:06:11,837
Not very Christian of me.

994
01:06:12,337 --> 01:06:13,839
You did what's right.

995
01:06:14,339 --> 01:06:18,385
Coming from you,
that means almost nothing.

996
01:06:23,974 --> 01:06:26,518
I'm long gone.
No, Doc will bring
you around.

997
01:06:26,602 --> 01:06:29,479
I look to be bored
by many more sermons
before you slip.

998
01:06:29,563 --> 01:06:30,814
Just don't move.

999
01:06:31,481 --> 01:06:33,275
Can't order me
around, boy.

1000
01:06:34,526 --> 01:06:36,320
I'm not one
of your crew.

1001
01:06:38,405 --> 01:06:39,823
Yes, you are.

1002
01:06:42,659 --> 01:06:44,494
River...
Come on.

1003
01:06:44,953 --> 01:06:45,954
Hey.

1004
01:06:47,706 --> 01:06:51,668
I don't care
what you believe.
Just believe it.

1005
01:06:53,337 --> 01:06:55,172
Whatever you...

1006
01:07:28,622 --> 01:07:30,666
How come
they ain't waiting?

1007
01:07:31,833 --> 01:07:34,795
They knowed we was coming,
how come they only sent one?

1008
01:07:35,921 --> 01:07:38,257
They didn't know
we were coming here.

1009
01:07:39,049 --> 01:07:40,759
Get on the Cortex.

1010
01:07:40,884 --> 01:07:42,719
Wave, Li Shen,
the Sanchez brothers...

1011
01:07:42,803 --> 01:07:46,306
anyone who has ever
sheltered us after a heist.
Tell them to get out.

1012
01:07:46,390 --> 01:07:47,599
Get out now.

1013
01:07:58,777 --> 01:07:59,945
I'm sorry.

1014
01:08:02,072 --> 01:08:05,868
If your quarry goes to ground,
leave no ground to go to.

1015
01:08:06,994 --> 01:08:08,996
You should have
taken my offer.

1016
01:08:09,079 --> 01:08:11,665
Or did you think none of this
was your fault?

1017
01:08:11,915 --> 01:08:13,917
I don't murder children.

1018
01:08:14,293 --> 01:08:15,294
I do.

1019
01:08:16,253 --> 01:08:18,255
If I have to.
Why?

1020
01:08:20,132 --> 01:08:22,301
Do you even know
why they sent you?

1021
01:08:23,093 --> 01:08:24,845
It's not my place to ask.

1022
01:08:26,096 --> 01:08:28,599
I believe in something
greater than myself.

1023
01:08:29,725 --> 01:08:31,101
A better world.

1024
01:08:31,768 --> 01:08:33,562
A world without sin.

1025
01:08:34,104 --> 01:08:36,106
So me and mine
gotta lay down and die...

1026
01:08:36,190 --> 01:08:38,400
so you can live
in your better world?

1027
01:08:38,859 --> 01:08:40,986
I'm not going to live there.

1028
01:08:41,403 --> 01:08:42,988
There's no place
for me there...

1029
01:08:43,071 --> 01:08:45,532
any more than
there is for you. Malcolm...

1030
01:08:45,699 --> 01:08:46,950
I'm a monster.

1031
01:08:48,619 --> 01:08:49,912
What I do is evil.

1032
01:08:49,995 --> 01:08:52,539
I have no illusions about it,
but it must be done.

1033
01:08:52,623 --> 01:08:54,082
Keep talking.

1034
01:08:54,416 --> 01:08:56,460
You're not getting
a location trace
off this wave.

1035
01:08:56,543 --> 01:09:00,422
And every minute
you keep River Tam from me,
more people will die.

1036
01:09:00,506 --> 01:09:03,008
You think I care?
Of course you care.

1037
01:09:03,967 --> 01:09:05,719
You're not a Reaver, Mal.

1038
01:09:06,220 --> 01:09:09,681
You're a human man
and you will never
understand how...

1039
01:09:15,938 --> 01:09:17,773
Get these bodies together.

1040
01:09:18,273 --> 01:09:19,608
(Zoe)
We got time
for grave digging?

1041
01:09:19,650 --> 01:09:21,151
Zoe, you and Simon
rope them together.

1042
01:09:21,235 --> 01:09:23,612
Five or six.
I want them laid out
on the nose of our ship.

1043
01:09:23,654 --> 01:09:24,780
Are you insane?

1044
01:09:24,863 --> 01:09:26,156
I won't desecrate
these bodies.

1045
01:09:26,240 --> 01:09:28,116
I don't understand.
What do you mean,
the bodies...

1046
01:09:28,158 --> 01:09:29,618
I want you to muck up
the reactor core.

1047
01:09:29,660 --> 01:09:31,703
Just enough to leave a trail
and make it read like...

1048
01:09:31,787 --> 01:09:33,914
we're flying
without containment,
not enough to fry us.

1049
01:09:33,997 --> 01:09:35,791
These people
are our friends.
Kaylee...

1050
01:09:35,874 --> 01:09:38,710
you got a day's work to do
and two hours to do it.

1051
01:09:39,753 --> 01:09:44,007
Jayne, you and Wash
hoist up the cannon mount.
Goes right on top.

1052
01:09:44,091 --> 01:09:45,759
Piece or two
of the other ship,
stick it on.

1053
01:09:45,801 --> 01:09:49,054
Any place you can tear hull
without inner breach,
do that, too.

1054
01:09:49,888 --> 01:09:53,141
We're gonna need paint.
We're gonna need red paint.

1055
01:09:53,642 --> 01:09:54,643
Sir...

1056
01:09:55,143 --> 01:09:58,564
do you really mean
to turn our home
into an abomination...

1057
01:09:58,647 --> 01:10:00,440
so that we can make
a suicidal attempt...

1058
01:10:00,524 --> 01:10:02,568
at passing through
Reaver space?

1059
01:10:02,651 --> 01:10:03,944
I mean to live.

1060
01:10:04,403 --> 01:10:05,821
[Man coughing]
I mean for us to live.

1061
01:10:05,904 --> 01:10:08,490
The Alliance won't have that,
so we go where
they don't follow.

1062
01:10:08,574 --> 01:10:10,742
God's balls,
there ain't no way
we're going out there.

1063
01:10:10,826 --> 01:10:12,494
Mal, think about
what you're asking.

1064
01:10:12,578 --> 01:10:14,788
(Jayne)
...those Reavers'll
eat us alive...

1065
01:10:16,498 --> 01:10:17,916
This is how it is.

1066
01:10:18,333 --> 01:10:20,043
Anybody doesn't wanna
fly with me anymore...

1067
01:10:20,127 --> 01:10:21,962
this is your port of harbor.

1068
01:10:22,838 --> 01:10:24,840
There's a lot
of fine ways to die.

1069
01:10:24,923 --> 01:10:27,634
I ain't waiting
for the Alliance
to choose mine.

1070
01:10:28,594 --> 01:10:29,761
[Gun firing]

1071
01:10:31,221 --> 01:10:32,681
I mean to confound
these bungers.

1072
01:10:32,764 --> 01:10:34,433
Take my shot
at getting to Miranda.

1073
01:10:34,474 --> 01:10:37,102
Maybe find something I can use
to get clear of this.

1074
01:10:37,144 --> 01:10:40,063
So I hear a word
out of any of you
that ain't helping me out...

1075
01:10:40,147 --> 01:10:42,608
or taking your leave,
I will shoot you down.

1076
01:10:47,571 --> 01:10:48,864
Get to work.

1077
01:11:14,389 --> 01:11:15,474
(Zoe)
Sir...

1078
01:11:15,516 --> 01:11:17,351
Just tell me
when we're close.

1079
01:11:53,011 --> 01:11:54,680
[People screaming]

1080
01:12:24,585 --> 01:12:25,544
(Mal)
Wash.

1081
01:13:30,192 --> 01:13:33,403
Define "disappeared."

1082
01:13:38,158 --> 01:13:40,410
(Zoe)
Every reading
I'm getting says normal.

1083
01:13:41,161 --> 01:13:44,498
Oceans, land masses.
No tectonic instability
or radiation.

1084
01:13:44,581 --> 01:13:47,543
Yeah, but no power,
either.
Nothing at all?

1085
01:13:47,626 --> 01:13:48,585
Wait.

1086
01:13:49,294 --> 01:13:50,379
Something.

1087
01:13:51,463 --> 01:13:53,924
It might be a beacon,
but it's awful weak.

1088
01:13:54,591 --> 01:13:56,009
Find it.

1089
01:14:04,309 --> 01:14:05,936
Gravity's Earthnorm.

1090
01:14:06,603 --> 01:14:08,856
O2 levels check,
pressure...

1091
01:14:09,606 --> 01:14:12,442
If anything's wrong
the scanner's
not reading it.

1092
01:14:18,282 --> 01:14:20,659
Well, something sure
the hell ain't right.

1093
01:14:23,620 --> 01:14:24,913
This ain't
no little settlement.

1094
01:14:24,955 --> 01:14:27,791
We flew over
at least a dozen
cities just as big.

1095
01:14:27,875 --> 01:14:30,127
Why didn't we ever
hear about this?

1096
01:14:30,294 --> 01:14:31,753
[Beeping]

1097
01:14:32,129 --> 01:14:33,505
Beacon's up ahead.

1098
01:14:56,570 --> 01:14:57,571
Ho.

1099
01:15:17,633 --> 01:15:20,010
No entry wounds,
fractures.

1100
01:15:20,469 --> 01:15:21,637
Poison?

1101
01:15:34,358 --> 01:15:35,984
Got another one.

1102
01:15:41,532 --> 01:15:43,242
They's just sitting here.

1103
01:15:44,952 --> 01:15:46,161
They didn't crash.

1104
01:15:47,454 --> 01:15:49,915
[Male announcer chattering]

1105
01:16:00,759 --> 01:16:02,302
Kaylee. Don't...

1106
01:16:02,386 --> 01:16:03,595
[screams]

1107
01:16:08,058 --> 01:16:10,310
How come these ones
are preserved?

1108
01:16:10,853 --> 01:16:12,980
Place must've gone hermetic
when the power blew.

1109
01:16:13,063 --> 01:16:15,691
Sealed them.
(Kaylee)
What are they doing?

1110
01:16:16,900 --> 01:16:18,819
What's everybody doing?

1111
01:16:19,027 --> 01:16:21,530
There's no unusual
discoloration.

1112
01:16:22,072 --> 01:16:24,825
Nobody's doubled over
or showing signs of pain.

1113
01:16:25,242 --> 01:16:27,536
(Mal)
There's gasses
that kill painless, right?

1114
01:16:27,870 --> 01:16:30,247
They didn't fall.
None of them.

1115
01:16:30,664 --> 01:16:32,374
They just lay down.

1116
01:16:32,583 --> 01:16:35,043
[River muttering in Chinese]

1117
01:16:36,128 --> 01:16:39,339
Make them stop.
They're everywhere.

1118
01:16:40,299 --> 01:16:42,426
Every city, every...

1119
01:16:42,718 --> 01:16:45,637
Every house, every room,
they're all inside me.

1120
01:16:45,721 --> 01:16:49,141
I can hear them all,
and they're saying nothing!

1121
01:16:50,184 --> 01:16:51,185
Get up.

1122
01:16:52,311 --> 01:16:53,770
Please get up.

1123
01:16:54,938 --> 01:16:56,773
[Speaking Chinese]

1124
01:16:58,567 --> 01:17:00,861
Please, God,
make me a stone.

1125
01:17:02,070 --> 01:17:03,906
She is starting
to damage my calm.

1126
01:17:03,989 --> 01:17:05,490
(Zoe)
Jayne.
She's right!

1127
01:17:06,533 --> 01:17:08,160
Everybody's dead.

1128
01:17:09,620 --> 01:17:11,914
This whole world is dead
for no reason!

1129
01:17:14,374 --> 01:17:16,251
Let's get to the beacon.

1130
01:17:42,277 --> 01:17:44,238
(Wash)
This is the source?

1131
01:17:47,574 --> 01:17:49,785
(Jayne)
This ship's banged up
all to hell.

1132
01:18:07,052 --> 01:18:09,847
These are just a few of
the few images we've recorded.

1133
01:18:10,931 --> 01:18:12,558
And you can see...

1134
01:18:14,184 --> 01:18:15,727
it isn't what we thought.

1135
01:18:17,312 --> 01:18:18,814
There's been no war here...

1136
01:18:19,815 --> 01:18:22,901
and no terraforming event.
The environment is stable.

1137
01:18:28,031 --> 01:18:29,449
It's the Pax.

1138
01:18:30,951 --> 01:18:35,289
The G-23 Paxilon Hydroclorate
that we added
to the air processors.

1139
01:18:36,290 --> 01:18:40,002
It was supposed to calm
the population,
weed out aggression.

1140
01:18:42,129 --> 01:18:43,755
Well, it works.

1141
01:18:44,631 --> 01:18:47,050
The people here
stopped fighting.

1142
01:18:48,010 --> 01:18:50,637
And then they stopped
everything else.

1143
01:18:55,559 --> 01:18:57,769
They stopped going to work...

1144
01:18:58,645 --> 01:19:02,900
they stopped breeding,
talking, eating.

1145
01:19:04,735 --> 01:19:08,989
There's 30 million people
here, and they all just
let themselves die.

1146
01:19:09,823 --> 01:19:10,866
[Crashing]

1147
01:19:10,949 --> 01:19:11,992
[Gasps]

1148
01:19:12,075 --> 01:19:13,493
I have to be quick.

1149
01:19:14,620 --> 01:19:16,288
About a tenth
of a percent of...

1150
01:19:16,330 --> 01:19:18,665
the population had
the opposite reaction
to the Pax.

1151
01:19:19,333 --> 01:19:22,961
Their aggressor response
increased beyond madness.

1152
01:19:23,462 --> 01:19:24,630
They have become...

1153
01:19:25,088 --> 01:19:26,924
[crashing]

1154
01:19:27,007 --> 01:19:28,634
Well, they've killed
most of us.

1155
01:19:29,760 --> 01:19:31,512
And not just killed...

1156
01:19:33,347 --> 01:19:35,098
they've done things.

1157
01:19:35,599 --> 01:19:38,727
Reavers. They made them.

1158
01:19:40,354 --> 01:19:44,483
I won't live to report this,
but people have to know.

1159
01:19:45,776 --> 01:19:47,569
We meant it for the best...

1160
01:19:48,028 --> 01:19:49,404
to make people safer.

1161
01:19:49,780 --> 01:19:51,156
[Reavers growling]

1162
01:19:51,198 --> 01:19:54,284
God!

1163
01:19:54,993 --> 01:19:56,703
[Woman screaming]

1164
01:19:56,787 --> 01:19:58,664
[Reaver growling]

1165
01:19:59,122 --> 01:20:00,999
Turn it off.

1166
01:20:05,879 --> 01:20:06,880
[Sobbing]

1167
01:20:20,477 --> 01:20:21,937
[Retching]

1168
01:20:25,691 --> 01:20:28,610
River.
I'm all right.

1169
01:20:36,618 --> 01:20:38,036
I'm all right.

1170
01:20:46,336 --> 01:20:48,755
(Mal)
This report is maybe
12 years old.

1171
01:20:49,756 --> 01:20:53,677
Parliament buried it,
and it stayed buried
till River dug it up.

1172
01:20:55,262 --> 01:20:57,723
This is what
they feared she knew.

1173
01:20:58,307 --> 01:21:00,184
And they were
right to fear...

1174
01:21:00,726 --> 01:21:03,729
because there's a whole
universe of folk
who are gonna know it, too.

1175
01:21:03,770 --> 01:21:05,397
They're gonna see it.

1176
01:21:06,023 --> 01:21:08,692
Somebody has to speak
for these people.

1177
01:21:12,112 --> 01:21:14,489
You all got on this boat
for different reasons...

1178
01:21:14,573 --> 01:21:16,700
but you all come
to the same place.

1179
01:21:17,117 --> 01:21:20,287
So now I'm asking more of you
than I have before.

1180
01:21:21,413 --> 01:21:22,748
Maybe all.

1181
01:21:24,750 --> 01:21:27,920
Sure as I know anything
I know this,
they will try again.

1182
01:21:29,296 --> 01:21:31,798
Maybe on another world,
maybe on this very ground
swept clean.

1183
01:21:31,924 --> 01:21:34,718
A year from now, 10,
they'll swing back
to the belief...

1184
01:21:34,843 --> 01:21:36,929
that they can make people...

1185
01:21:39,681 --> 01:21:40,682
better.

1186
01:21:43,852 --> 01:21:45,854
And I do not hold to that.

1187
01:21:48,190 --> 01:21:49,608
So no more running.

1188
01:21:52,152 --> 01:21:53,862
I aim to misbehave.

1189
01:22:01,662 --> 01:22:03,914
Shepherd Book
used to tell me:

1190
01:22:04,039 --> 01:22:06,083
"If you can't do
something smart...

1191
01:22:07,584 --> 01:22:09,419
"do something right."

1192
01:22:10,671 --> 01:22:13,382
Do we have a plan?
Mr. Universe.

1193
01:22:13,966 --> 01:22:16,009
We haven't the equipment
to broadwave this code...

1194
01:22:16,093 --> 01:22:18,554
but he can put it
on every screen for 30 worlds.

1195
01:22:19,179 --> 01:22:20,931
He's pretty damn close, too.

1196
01:22:21,473 --> 01:22:22,558
We still got the Reavers...

1197
01:22:22,641 --> 01:22:24,893
and probably the Alliance,
between us and him.

1198
01:22:25,185 --> 01:22:27,896
(Jayne)
That's two armies against
our one bitty cannon.

1199
01:22:28,105 --> 01:22:31,066
It's a fair bet
the Alliance knows
about Mr. Universe.

1200
01:22:31,149 --> 01:22:32,609
They're gonna
see this coming.

1201
01:22:33,777 --> 01:22:34,736
No.

1202
01:22:36,822 --> 01:22:39,116
They're not gonna
see this coming.

1203
01:22:40,075 --> 01:22:41,577
[Engine revving]

1204
01:22:47,374 --> 01:22:49,293
No problem. Bring it on.
Bring it on. Bring it on.

1205
01:22:49,751 --> 01:22:52,379
From here to the eyes
and ears of the 'verse.
That's my motto...

1206
01:22:52,462 --> 01:22:54,840
or it might be,
if I start having a motto.

1207
01:22:54,923 --> 01:22:55,924
We won't be long.

1208
01:22:56,008 --> 01:22:58,010
You're going to get caught
in the ion cloud.

1209
01:22:58,093 --> 01:22:59,720
It'll play merry hob
with your radar...

1210
01:22:59,803 --> 01:23:02,639
but pretty lights
and a few miles after
you'll be right in my orbit.

1211
01:23:02,723 --> 01:23:04,933
You'll let us know
if anyone else comes at you?

1212
01:23:05,017 --> 01:23:06,768
You'll be the first.

1213
01:23:12,816 --> 01:23:13,984
There.

1214
01:23:14,234 --> 01:23:16,570
Toss me my 30 coin,
but I got a newswave for you...

1215
01:23:16,820 --> 01:23:18,113
[gasping]

1216
01:23:26,663 --> 01:23:29,791
Call in every ship
in the quadrant.
We'll meet them in the air.

1217
01:23:31,418 --> 01:23:32,920
Destroy it all.

1218
01:23:59,655 --> 01:24:02,074
(Mal)
Wash, we almost through?

1219
01:24:24,054 --> 01:24:25,055
Now!

1220
01:24:30,602 --> 01:24:32,271
(Wash)
Go! Move!

1221
01:24:51,957 --> 01:24:56,128
I'm reading activity
in the cloud.
Lock and fire on my command.

1222
01:24:58,255 --> 01:25:00,549
You should have
let me see her, Captain.

1223
01:25:01,717 --> 01:25:05,512
We should have done this
as men. Not with fire.

1224
01:25:05,888 --> 01:25:07,097
(helmsman)
Sir.

1225
01:25:07,222 --> 01:25:08,223
[Electronic beeping]

1226
01:25:12,311 --> 01:25:14,062
Vessel in range.
Lock on.

1227
01:25:21,987 --> 01:25:23,906
Bastard's not even
changing course.

1228
01:25:29,036 --> 01:25:30,037
Sir!

1229
01:25:33,665 --> 01:25:36,752
Target the Reavers.
Target the Reavers!

1230
01:25:36,835 --> 01:25:39,129
Target everyone!
Somebody fire!

1231
01:25:56,688 --> 01:26:00,984
I am a leaf on the wind.
Watch how I soar.

1232
01:26:15,415 --> 01:26:17,125
Chicken's come home
to roost.

1233
01:26:18,585 --> 01:26:20,671
The hell?
It's okay.

1234
01:26:20,921 --> 01:26:23,215
I am a leaf on the wind!
What does that mean?

1235
01:26:27,427 --> 01:26:28,929
We're almost through.

1236
01:26:45,612 --> 01:26:48,031
No! No! No!
Yes! Yes!

1237
01:27:25,110 --> 01:27:26,111
[Rumbling]

1238
01:27:41,001 --> 01:27:42,461
We're not alone.

1239
01:27:50,093 --> 01:27:51,136
EMP!

1240
01:27:51,220 --> 01:27:52,971
Everybody, strap yourselves
into something!

1241
01:27:53,055 --> 01:27:54,056
Jayne.
(Jayne)
Got it.

1242
01:27:55,390 --> 01:27:57,100
Kaylee, come on.

1243
01:28:09,905 --> 01:28:12,324
We're fried.
I got no control.
Where's the backup?

1244
01:28:12,866 --> 01:28:14,910
Where's the backup?

1245
01:28:22,292 --> 01:28:23,669
Check! Check!

1246
01:28:23,752 --> 01:28:25,337
[Engine whining]

1247
01:28:25,879 --> 01:28:27,506
[Jayne screaming]

1248
01:28:40,769 --> 01:28:41,770
[Whooshing]

1249
01:28:48,402 --> 01:28:49,444
(Mal)
Get up!

1250
01:28:49,528 --> 01:28:50,821
(Kaylee)
Stop it!

1251
01:28:55,909 --> 01:28:57,995
Backup reads at 20%.
Can you get us down?

1252
01:28:58,078 --> 01:29:01,123
I'm going to have
to glide her in.
Will that work?

1253
01:29:11,800 --> 01:29:13,177
[Screaming]

1254
01:29:45,042 --> 01:29:46,043
[Panting]

1255
01:29:55,928 --> 01:29:57,679
I am a leaf on the wind.

1256
01:30:00,057 --> 01:30:01,850
Watch how...

1257
01:30:01,892 --> 01:30:02,893
[gasps]

1258
01:30:03,936 --> 01:30:08,398
Wash, baby. Baby, no.
Baby, come on.
You gotta go. Come on.

1259
01:30:08,482 --> 01:30:12,152
We gotta move. Baby, please.
We gotta move, baby, come on.

1260
01:30:15,489 --> 01:30:16,490
(Mal)
Zoe!

1261
01:30:17,741 --> 01:30:19,493
Move out! Now!

1262
01:30:23,539 --> 01:30:24,540
Go. Go.

1263
01:30:25,249 --> 01:30:26,542
Head inside!

1264
01:30:45,602 --> 01:30:47,187
Jayne, rearguard.

1265
01:30:54,862 --> 01:30:57,030
Zoe, what've we got?
(Zoe)
Sir...

1266
01:30:59,032 --> 01:31:00,284
this is a good hold point.

1267
01:31:00,617 --> 01:31:02,244
We all stay together.
No.

1268
01:31:02,327 --> 01:31:03,537
They have to come
through here.

1269
01:31:03,579 --> 01:31:05,497
They'll bottleneck,
we can thin them out.

1270
01:31:05,622 --> 01:31:08,417
We get pushed back,
there's the blast doors.

1271
01:31:08,542 --> 01:31:10,836
I can rig them
so they won't reopen
once they close.

1272
01:31:10,919 --> 01:31:11,962
Shut them
and hide until I get...

1273
01:31:12,045 --> 01:31:13,964
We need to draw them
till it's done.

1274
01:31:15,132 --> 01:31:17,509
This is the place.
We'll buy you the time.

1275
01:31:22,389 --> 01:31:24,808
All right, let's move
those crates back there
for cover.

1276
01:31:24,892 --> 01:31:27,352
Make sure they ain't filled
with nothing goes boom.

1277
01:31:27,686 --> 01:31:29,730
Wait, Wash!
Where's Wash?

1278
01:31:30,856 --> 01:31:32,441
He ain't coming.

1279
01:31:37,613 --> 01:31:39,656
Move the gorramn crates!

1280
01:31:52,669 --> 01:31:54,296
[Reavers howling]

1281
01:31:57,341 --> 01:31:59,843
Tell me you brought them
this time.

1282
01:32:00,177 --> 01:32:01,803
[Reavers growling]

1283
01:32:08,018 --> 01:32:09,353
[Explosion]

1284
01:32:13,815 --> 01:32:14,775
[Grunting]

1285
01:32:22,533 --> 01:32:23,784
Zoe?

1286
01:32:25,994 --> 01:32:28,622
Are you here?
Do the job, sir.

1287
01:32:31,166 --> 01:32:33,794
You hold.
Hold till I get back.

1288
01:32:37,881 --> 01:32:38,924
Captain's right.

1289
01:32:39,007 --> 01:32:42,052
Can't be thinking on revenge
if we're gonna
get through this.

1290
01:32:42,135 --> 01:32:44,763
Do you really think
any of us are gonna
get through this?

1291
01:32:48,350 --> 01:32:49,351
I might.

1292
01:33:04,616 --> 01:33:06,034
[Static crackling]

1293
01:33:06,410 --> 01:33:07,411
No.

1294
01:33:28,974 --> 01:33:29,975
Mal.

1295
01:33:30,851 --> 01:33:32,561
Guy killed me, Mal.

1296
01:33:32,936 --> 01:33:36,148
He killed me with a sword.
How weird is that?

1297
01:33:37,024 --> 01:33:40,944
I got a short span here.

1298
01:33:42,404 --> 01:33:44,156
They destroyed my equipment...

1299
01:33:44,531 --> 01:33:46,074
but I have a backup unit.

1300
01:33:46,158 --> 01:33:48,535
Bottom of the complex,
right over the generator.

1301
01:33:49,036 --> 01:33:52,164
Hard to get to.
I know they missed it.

1302
01:33:52,956 --> 01:33:55,167
They can't stop
the signal, Mal.

1303
01:33:56,043 --> 01:33:58,462
They can never
stop the signal.

1304
01:33:58,545 --> 01:34:00,339
[Reavers growling]

1305
01:34:02,716 --> 01:34:05,052
The Reavers.
They are all made up of rage.

1306
01:34:05,135 --> 01:34:07,930
It's okay. It's okay.
I can't shut them up.

1307
01:34:08,555 --> 01:34:10,265
[Banging on door]

1308
01:34:11,725 --> 01:34:12,893
Stay low.

1309
01:34:13,435 --> 01:34:16,897
She picked a sweet
bung of a time
to go helpless on us.

1310
01:34:18,106 --> 01:34:19,233
Jayne and I take
the first wave.

1311
01:34:19,316 --> 01:34:21,818
Nobody shoots unless
they get past our fire.

1312
01:34:25,697 --> 01:34:28,325
I didn't plan
on going out like this.

1313
01:34:30,160 --> 01:34:32,371
I think we did right, but...

1314
01:34:33,413 --> 01:34:37,709
No. I never planned...
anything.

1315
01:34:39,711 --> 01:34:41,880
I just wanted
to keep River safe.

1316
01:34:45,634 --> 01:34:49,304
Spent so much time on Serenity
ignoring anything...

1317
01:34:50,264 --> 01:34:52,766
that I wanted for myself.

1318
01:34:57,521 --> 01:34:59,898
My one regret
in all of this...

1319
01:35:01,233 --> 01:35:02,943
is never being with you.

1320
01:35:05,028 --> 01:35:06,363
With me?

1321
01:35:08,156 --> 01:35:10,158
You mean to say, as...

1322
01:35:12,077 --> 01:35:13,203
Sex?

1323
01:35:15,455 --> 01:35:17,249
I mean to say.

1324
01:35:18,417 --> 01:35:19,751
[Metal squeaks]

1325
01:35:22,254 --> 01:35:25,382
Hell with this.
I'm gonna live.

1326
01:35:39,271 --> 01:35:42,649
Mal. Guy killed me, Mal.

1327
01:35:43,775 --> 01:35:45,402
He killed me with a sword.

1328
01:36:01,710 --> 01:36:03,212
[Reavers growling]

1329
01:36:24,149 --> 01:36:25,734
"Hard to get to."

1330
01:36:26,985 --> 01:36:28,695
That's a fact.

1331
01:36:35,953 --> 01:36:37,454
Zoe, gorrammit!

1332
01:36:38,163 --> 01:36:39,790
[Reavers shrieking]

1333
01:36:45,921 --> 01:36:46,922
[Screams]

1334
01:36:53,345 --> 01:36:55,681
Zoe, get your ass
back on the line!

1335
01:36:56,640 --> 01:36:57,808
[Screams]

1336
01:37:09,528 --> 01:37:10,904
[Groaning]

1337
01:37:12,155 --> 01:37:13,866
You shot me in the back!

1338
01:37:15,534 --> 01:37:17,995
I haven't made you
angry, have I?

1339
01:37:18,036 --> 01:37:21,206
There are a lot
of innocent people in the air
being killed right now.

1340
01:37:21,290 --> 01:37:23,709
You have no idea
how true that is.

1341
01:37:25,169 --> 01:37:26,795
I know the secret.

1342
01:37:27,588 --> 01:37:30,048
The truth that burned up
River Tam's brain.

1343
01:37:30,841 --> 01:37:34,887
Rest of the 'verse
is going to know it, too.
'Cause they need to.

1344
01:37:36,847 --> 01:37:40,142
Do you really believe that?
I do.

1345
01:37:40,559 --> 01:37:42,686
You willing to die
for that belief?

1346
01:37:45,105 --> 01:37:46,315
I am.

1347
01:37:48,984 --> 01:37:49,943
[Screams]

1348
01:37:50,027 --> 01:37:51,028
[Gun firing]

1349
01:37:53,071 --> 01:37:55,157
Of course,
that ain't exactly Plan A.

1350
01:38:01,371 --> 01:38:02,456
[Groaning]

1351
01:38:20,265 --> 01:38:21,266
[Gun firing]

1352
01:38:21,767 --> 01:38:23,894
Spine's intact.
Just give me a bandage.

1353
01:38:26,271 --> 01:38:27,523
[Gasping]

1354
01:38:54,758 --> 01:38:56,301
[Grunting]

1355
01:39:05,227 --> 01:39:06,562
[Both grunting]

1356
01:39:14,570 --> 01:39:15,571
[Sobbing]

1357
01:39:17,573 --> 01:39:18,991
(Jayne)
Up high, left!

1358
01:39:23,829 --> 01:39:24,830
[Groans]

1359
01:39:25,622 --> 01:39:26,665
[Gasps]

1360
01:39:26,748 --> 01:39:28,167
Kaylee!

1361
01:39:37,426 --> 01:39:38,385
[Screaming]

1362
01:39:40,804 --> 01:39:44,766
Fall back! Everybody,
fall back! Fall back now!

1363
01:39:54,359 --> 01:39:55,652
Jayne, grenade.

1364
01:39:56,987 --> 01:39:59,198
Very last one.

1365
01:40:05,245 --> 01:40:06,330
They're gonna get in.

1366
01:40:06,663 --> 01:40:09,374
I can close it
from the outside.

1367
01:40:09,791 --> 01:40:11,752
No one's coming
back from that.

1368
01:40:14,796 --> 01:40:16,715
How much ammo
do we have?

1369
01:40:16,798 --> 01:40:20,719
Three, four max,
and my swinging cod.
That's all.

1370
01:40:20,761 --> 01:40:21,803
The lift isn't moving.

1371
01:40:21,887 --> 01:40:24,348
When they come,
try to plug
the hole with it.

1372
01:40:24,431 --> 01:40:26,850
I'm starting to lose
some feeling here.

1373
01:40:26,934 --> 01:40:29,603
Lie still. I'm going
to give you something...

1374
01:40:31,647 --> 01:40:32,648
My bag.

1375
01:40:32,731 --> 01:40:33,732
[Gun fires]

1376
01:40:37,152 --> 01:40:38,946
[Gun firing]

1377
01:40:42,950 --> 01:40:44,493
Keep pressure here.

1378
01:40:46,286 --> 01:40:47,246
(Simon)
My bag.

1379
01:40:47,788 --> 01:40:48,789
I need...

1380
01:40:49,623 --> 01:40:53,085
adrenaline and a shot of...

1381
01:40:53,627 --> 01:40:55,212
calaphar for Kaylee.

1382
01:40:57,923 --> 01:40:59,591
[Gasping]
I can't.

1383
01:41:03,470 --> 01:41:04,471
River.

1384
01:41:09,560 --> 01:41:12,271
River, I'm sorry.
No.

1385
01:41:13,647 --> 01:41:14,773
No.

1386
01:41:21,947 --> 01:41:24,158
I hate to leave.
You won't.

1387
01:41:27,119 --> 01:41:29,705
You take care of me, Simon.

1388
01:41:32,791 --> 01:41:35,419
You've always
taken care of me.

1389
01:41:40,757 --> 01:41:41,884
My turn.

1390
01:41:59,359 --> 01:42:01,153
[Operative and Mal grunting]

1391
01:42:36,772 --> 01:42:39,399
Do you know
what your sin is, Mal?

1392
01:42:39,983 --> 01:42:43,362
Hell. I'm a fan
of all seven.

1393
01:42:43,737 --> 01:42:44,738
[Groans]

1394
01:42:49,868 --> 01:42:51,662
But right now...

1395
01:42:52,704 --> 01:42:54,706
I'm going to have
to go with wrath.

1396
01:42:59,169 --> 01:43:01,630
We ain't got long.

1397
01:43:03,841 --> 01:43:04,842
[Thudding]

1398
01:43:07,678 --> 01:43:09,555
You suppose he got through?

1399
01:43:10,806 --> 01:43:12,766
Do you think Mal
got the word out?

1400
01:43:13,433 --> 01:43:17,855
He got through.
I know he got through.

1401
01:43:18,856 --> 01:43:20,023
[Groans]

1402
01:43:20,399 --> 01:43:21,942
[Coughs]

1403
01:43:29,116 --> 01:43:30,117
I'm sorry.

1404
01:43:30,200 --> 01:43:31,160
[Groans]

1405
01:43:33,412 --> 01:43:36,206
You should know
there's no shame in this.

1406
01:43:38,417 --> 01:43:40,544
You've done remarkable things.

1407
01:43:41,753 --> 01:43:43,964
But you're fighting a war...

1408
01:43:45,174 --> 01:43:46,383
you've already lost.

1409
01:43:47,467 --> 01:43:48,635
[Groans]

1410
01:43:49,887 --> 01:43:50,846
[Gasping]

1411
01:43:51,221 --> 01:43:53,098
Well, I'm known for that.

1412
01:43:55,017 --> 01:43:56,018
[Groaning]

1413
01:44:02,024 --> 01:44:05,652
Piece of shrapnel tore up
that nerve cluster
my first tour.

1414
01:44:06,236 --> 01:44:07,571
Had it moved.

1415
01:44:09,156 --> 01:44:10,574
Sorry about the throat.

1416
01:44:11,200 --> 01:44:14,036
Expect you'd want to say your
famous last words right now.

1417
01:44:15,078 --> 01:44:16,663
Just one trouble.

1418
01:44:21,418 --> 01:44:22,878
I ain't gonna kill you.

1419
01:44:23,545 --> 01:44:24,838
[Gasping]

1420
01:44:26,381 --> 01:44:29,468
Hell, I'm gonna grant
your greatest wish.

1421
01:44:31,178 --> 01:44:32,179
[Beeping]

1422
01:44:36,808 --> 01:44:39,645
I'm gonna show you
a world without sin.

1423
01:44:45,484 --> 01:44:47,569
These are just a few of
the few images we've recorded.

1424
01:44:47,611 --> 01:44:48,612
And you can see...

1425
01:44:51,532 --> 01:44:53,700
it isn't what we thought.

1426
01:44:55,410 --> 01:44:57,287
There's been no war here...

1427
01:44:57,955 --> 01:45:02,251
and no terraforming event.
The environment is stable.

1428
01:45:03,919 --> 01:45:05,671
It's the Pax.

1429
01:45:07,339 --> 01:45:11,677
The G-23 Paxilon Hydroclorate
that we added
to the air processors.

1430
01:45:12,386 --> 01:45:14,972
It was supposed to calm
the population...

1431
01:45:15,097 --> 01:45:16,515
[roaring]

1432
01:45:43,584 --> 01:45:45,252
We meant it for the best...

1433
01:45:46,170 --> 01:45:47,713
to make people safer.

1434
01:45:47,796 --> 01:45:49,423
[Reavers growling]

1435
01:45:49,464 --> 01:45:50,799
God!

1436
01:45:52,801 --> 01:45:54,219
[Woman screaming]

1437
01:45:54,303 --> 01:45:55,929
[Reaver growling]

1438
01:46:07,357 --> 01:46:08,358
[Panting]

1439
01:46:13,655 --> 01:46:16,116
Sir?
It's done.

1440
01:46:19,286 --> 01:46:20,621
Report.

1441
01:46:22,789 --> 01:46:23,957
River?

1442
01:46:49,525 --> 01:46:50,484
(soldier #1)
Drop your weapons!

1443
01:46:50,567 --> 01:46:51,610
(soldier #2)
Do it now.

1444
01:46:51,693 --> 01:46:53,153
Weapons down.
Let it down, now.

1445
01:46:53,195 --> 01:46:54,821
I want to see
your hands in the air.

1446
01:46:54,863 --> 01:46:56,740
Stand down.
Do it.

1447
01:47:02,204 --> 01:47:03,705
Targets are acquired.

1448
01:47:03,747 --> 01:47:05,165
Do we have a kill order?

1449
01:47:08,126 --> 01:47:09,878
Do we have an order?

1450
01:47:18,053 --> 01:47:19,304
(Operative)
Stand down.

1451
01:47:20,430 --> 01:47:23,183
Stand down. It's finished.

1452
01:47:26,979 --> 01:47:28,355
We're finished.

1453
01:49:30,727 --> 01:49:32,604
It's not over,
you know.

1454
01:49:34,314 --> 01:49:36,984
I can't guarantee
that they won't
come after you.

1455
01:49:37,818 --> 01:49:38,819
The Parliament.

1456
01:49:39,695 --> 01:49:42,698
Your broadwave about Miranda
has weakened their regime.

1457
01:49:42,781 --> 01:49:47,119
They are not gone
and they are not... forgiving.

1458
01:49:47,703 --> 01:49:50,164
That don't bode
especially well for you...

1459
01:49:50,914 --> 01:49:53,917
giving the order to let us go,
patching up our hurt.

1460
01:49:55,294 --> 01:49:58,755
I told them the Tams
were no longer a threat,
damage done.

1461
01:49:59,298 --> 01:50:00,799
They might listen...

1462
01:50:01,550 --> 01:50:04,970
but I think they know
I'm no longer their man.

1463
01:50:06,722 --> 01:50:09,808
They take you down,
I don't expect
to grieve over much.

1464
01:50:12,060 --> 01:50:14,479
Like to kill you myself,
I see you again.

1465
01:50:15,314 --> 01:50:16,315
You won't.

1466
01:50:19,276 --> 01:50:21,445
There is nothing left to see.

1467
01:50:27,159 --> 01:50:28,702
Sir, we have
a green light.

1468
01:50:29,119 --> 01:50:31,330
Inspection's pos
and we're clear
for up-thrust.

1469
01:50:37,836 --> 01:50:39,963
Think she'll hold together?

1470
01:50:40,964 --> 01:50:43,592
She's tore up plenty.
But she'll fly true.

1471
01:50:47,888 --> 01:50:50,140
Make sure
everything's secure.

1472
01:50:52,017 --> 01:50:54,895
Could be bumpy.
Always is.

1473
01:51:02,319 --> 01:51:03,320
Taking her out...

1474
01:51:03,403 --> 01:51:05,989
should be about a day's ride
to get you back to your girls.

1475
01:51:06,031 --> 01:51:07,199
Right.

1476
01:51:08,617 --> 01:51:10,828
Ready to get off this heap,
back to civilized life?

1477
01:51:10,911 --> 01:51:11,912
I, uh...

1478
01:51:16,708 --> 01:51:18,043
I don't know.

1479
01:51:20,045 --> 01:51:21,213
Good answer.

1480
01:51:46,446 --> 01:51:48,991
So, you gonna ride
shotgun with me,
help me fly?

1481
01:51:49,199 --> 01:51:50,450
That's the plan.

1482
01:51:51,118 --> 01:51:52,661
Think you can work out...

